description.narrative: Overall, 2,602,479 children (86% coverage) were reached with assistance in humanitarian contexts in the DRC through the various UNICEF's responses to emergencies. RRMP has reached its highest quality standards in terms satisfaction of affected populations and timeliness of the response. A reported 95% of households that have received emergency assistance provided by UNICEF were satisfied with the assistance received, compared to 90% in 2018 and 80% in 2017. In addition, 61% of RRMP targeted internally displaced persons (IDPs) sheltered with host families were assisted within 45 days after the humanitarian alerts, compared to 60 days in 2018. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
